description: The molecule is an indole alkaloid. It has a role as an antiparkinson drug, a hormone antagonist, a dopamine agonist and an antidyskinesia agent. It derives from a hydride of an ergotaman.
answer: The molecule is a steroidal lactam consisting of a steroid framework with a 5-membered lactam ring fused to it. The compound is likely to be a synthetic intermediate or a pharmacologically active agent. It is a member of bromopyrroles, an organobromine compound, and an azabicyclo alkane.

It has conjugated double bonds spanning the fatty acid chain, with the configuration given by the stereochemistry and geometric descriptors in the structure.

It is a pyranosyl oligosaccharide where the terminal sugar residue is a N-acetylglucosamine. It has a role as a plant metabolite and an allergen. It is an acetylated amino sugar derivative and an azasugar. It derives from an N-acetyl-D-glucosamine. It is a conjugate acid of a N-acetyl-D-glucosamine(1-).

description: The molecule is an organic heteropentacyclic compound, a delta-lactone, an acetate ester and a cyclic ketone. It has a role as an EC 2.7.1.137 (phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase) inhibitor and an anticoronaviral agent.
answer: The molecule is a tetracyclic polyketide that is derived from a A-ring-fused tetrahydrofuran, with an unsubstituted B-ring lactone and a 6,6-bicyclic ketone moiety. It is a structurally complex macrolide and a member of depsipeptides. It originates from a series of oxidation, methylation, and cyclization reactions of simpler polyketide precursors. It participates in biosynthetic pathways as an intermediate and serves a role as an antifungal antibiotic.

It carries a methylene bridge connecting to a chlorophenyl moiety and features a structural motif resembling purines with an attached isopropyl group. description: The molecule is a member of the class of tetracenomycins that is 8-demethyltetracenomycin C in which the hydroxyl hydrogens at position 8 and 10 a are replaced by a 2,3,4-tri-O-methyl-alpha-L-rhamnosyl and methyl groups respectively. answer: The molecule is a tetracyclic diterpenoid compound that comprises four hexahydro monosaccharide units that are assembled into the backbone of the molecule, with the structure being further modified by the presence of several acetate groups. This compound is biosynthetically derived from the diterpene class and its structure suggests possible roles in biological processes as secondary metabolites or signal transducers due to the presence of functional groups that can engage in various molecular interactions.

description: The molecule is a cyclic peptide antibiotic produced by a strain of Streptomyces toyocaensis. It has a role as a fungal metabolite. It is a heterodetic cyclic peptide, a cyclic ether, an organochlorine compound, a polyphenol, a peptide antibiotic and an aryl sulfate. It is a conjugate acid of an A47934(2-).
answer: The molecule is a cyclic peptide, specifically a glycopeptide antibiotic, which stems from a series of lengthy chemical reactions and structural modifications. It displays several types of chemical groups, including chlorination and hydroxylation, which aid in its antibiotic activity by increasing its affinity for certain bacterial elements. The compound is characterized by multiple amide bonds, which are indicative of peptide structures, along with several ether linkages and a sulfonate ester. The chlorinated aromatic groups and the presence of multiple hydroxyl groups contribute to its ability to interact with biological tissues, notably targeting bacterial cell walls. It has been utilized in clinical settings as a potent antibiotic against gram-positive organisms and is derived from extensive organic synthesis procedures, often involving complex biosynthetic pathways associated with antibiotic production. It is also notable for containing the unique amino acid residues which grant selectivity in binding, offering utility in combatting resistant bacterial strains.

description: The molecule is the stable isotope of magnesium with relative atomic mass 24.985837, 10.0 atom percent natural abundance and nuclear spin 5/2.

It is a tetracyclic triterpenoid, a steroid lactone, a polyol, and an organic heterotetracyclic compound.

description: The molecule is a primary fatty amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (9Z)-hexadecenoic acid with ammonia. It has a role as a fungal metabolite and a human metabolite. It derives from a palmitoleic acid.
answer: The molecule is a long-chain fatty amide. It is composed of a straight-chain aliphatic hydrocarbon with a terminal amide functional group, resulting from the formal condensation of a fatty acid with ammonia. This molecule is an example of an unsaturated fatty amide, due to the presence of a carbon-carbon double bond in the hydrocarbon chain. It is commonly found in biological systems and plays a role as a signaling molecule. It is a member of amides, specifically a monounsaturated fatty acid amide, and performs functions related to lipid metabolism.

description: The molecule is the fundamental parent of a class of sesquiterpenes with a structure based upon a cyclodecane ring substituted with an isopropyl and two methyl groups. It is a terpenoid fundamental parent and a sesquiterpene.
answer: The molecule is a terpenoid that is a member of the monocyclic sesquiterpenoids, with carbon branches featuring methyl groups. It is achiral but has chiral centers, implying the existence of stereoisomers. As a sesquiterpenoid, it is part of the larger class of isoprenoids, which are derived from the five-carbon isoprene units, characteristic of many natural products with diverse roles in biology.

description: The molecule is a guaiacyl lignin obtained by cyclodimerisation of coniferol. It has a role as a plant metabolite and an anti-inflammatory agent. It is a member of 1-benzofurans, a primary alcohol, a guaiacyl lignin and a member of guaiacols. It derives from a coniferol.
answer: The molecule is a member of the class of flavonoids known as isoflavones, characterized by a chromene ring system substituted with a 7-hydroxy-2,3-dihydrobenzofuran moiety. It is a naturally occurring compound that has a phenolic structure, playing a role in plant pigmentation, UV protection, and as an antioxidant. This compound typically contributes to the health benefits associated with diets rich in soy and other plants. It has a role as a plant metabolite and an antioxidant.

description: The molecule is an unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 8,9-epoxy-(5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid. It is a long-chain fatty acyl-CoA and an unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA. It derives from an 8,9-EET. It is a conjugate acid of an 8,9-epoxy-(5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl-CoA(4-).

description: The molecule is a Glu-Cys-Gly tripeptide derivative of glutathione containing a 2-hydroxyethyl substituent on the S of the Cys residue. It derives from a glutathione.
answer: The molecule is a tripeptide consisting of L-aspartic acid, L-cysteine, and glycine. It features an amide bond between the α-carboxylic acid group of L-aspartic acid and the α-amino group of L-cysteine, and another amide bond formed between the α-carboxylic acid group of L-cysteine and the amino group of glycine. It is a conjugate acid of a glutathione(1-). It has a role as an antioxidant, a cofactor, and a metabolite.

description: The molecule is a pyrrolopyrimidine that is 7-methyl-7H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidin-4-amine which has been substituted at position 5 by a 4-fluoro-2,3-dihydro-1H-indol-5-yl group, the nitrogen of which has been acylated by a (6-methylpyridin-2-yl)acetyl group. An orally bioavailable PERK inhibitor. It has a role as an EC 3.1.3.48 (protein-tyrosine-phosphatase) inhibitor, a PERK inhibitor and an antineoplastic agent. It is a pyrrolopyrimidine, a biaryl, a member of indoles, a member of methylpyridines, an organofluorine compound and a tertiary carboxamide.
